WEBVTT

00:02.176 --> 00:03.873
- Previously on
"The Baker and the Beauty"...

00:03.916 --> 00:06.528
- Ay, Abuela and I, we had such
a fun time planning my quinces.

00:06.571 --> 00:08.573
Turned out to be one
of the best days of my life.

00:08.617 --> 00:11.402
- But you're nothing special.
Your work is derivative.

00:11.446 --> 00:13.535
- It's over.
- Put these back on.

00:13.578 --> 00:16.755
[upbeat music]

00:16.799 --> 00:19.236
- Lewis!

00:19.280 --> 00:22.805
Because as of now, you're
gonna let me take care of you.

00:22.848 --> 00:24.328
- The surgery went well.

00:24.372 --> 00:26.678
I'm confident
we got the entire tumor.

00:26.722 --> 00:29.551
You were sick
and I didn't even notice.

00:29.594 --> 00:31.379
Since we've been together,

00:31.422 --> 00:33.381
your family's fighting,

00:33.424 --> 00:35.035
the bakery's in trouble...

00:35.078 --> 00:37.167
- Asbestos?
- It has to be removed.

00:37.211 --> 00:40.388
- You got arrested,
I almost lost my company.

00:40.431 --> 00:43.304
I think we need to stop seeing
each other, Daniel.

00:43.347 --> 00:45.349
[downbeat notes]

00:45.393 --> 00:47.525
- Every culture
has its own way

00:47.569 --> 00:51.051
of making the transition
from childhood to adulthood.

00:51.094 --> 00:54.837
Confirmation, bat mitzvah,
sweet 16,

00:54.880 --> 00:58.406
and in our case,
a quinceañera,

00:58.449 --> 01:00.712
a girl who's 15.

01:00.756 --> 01:03.150
It's a rite of passage.

01:03.193 --> 01:04.673
Aside from your wedding,

01:04.716 --> 01:07.284
it's supposed to be
the biggest day of your life,

01:07.328 --> 01:10.113
and mine
has been my mom's obsession

01:10.157 --> 01:12.333
since the day I was born.

01:12.376 --> 01:14.813
[dramatic Latin music]

01:14.857 --> 01:16.163
[crowd cheering]

01:16.206 --> 01:19.383
A quince
is all about spectacle.

01:19.427 --> 01:22.517
The perfect dress,
perfect hair.

01:22.560 --> 01:25.128
It's a night for everyone
to celebrate,

01:25.172 --> 01:28.436
to cut loose,
to forget their troubles.

01:28.479 --> 01:30.873
♪

01:30.916 --> 01:34.137
But my quince has
to do more than that.

01:34.181 --> 01:36.400
My qince has to fix my family.

01:36.444 --> 01:38.402
[soft dramatic music]

01:38.446 --> 01:40.404
My parents are on the edge

01:40.448 --> 01:44.582
because the bakery's
still closed.

01:44.626 --> 01:46.671
Mateo's life
has been complicated

01:46.715 --> 01:48.499
since he kissed Vanessa.

01:48.543 --> 01:52.590
And he hasn't smiled since
he stopped making music.

01:52.634 --> 01:54.157
♪

01:54.201 --> 01:57.204
And Daniel's making
cookie pizzas at Duffigan's

01:57.247 --> 01:58.727
to help make ends meet,

01:58.770 --> 02:01.425
and to try
to take his mind off Noa.

02:01.469 --> 02:03.775
But how is he supposed
to forget a woman

02:03.819 --> 02:05.386
who is everywhere?

02:05.429 --> 02:07.170
[spoon whacks loudly]

02:07.214 --> 02:11.305
- So your parents, Mateo's
music, Daniel's love life,

02:11.348 --> 02:13.916
how is one party supposed
to fix all of that?

02:13.959 --> 02:15.874
- I don't know,

02:15.918 --> 02:18.877
but my quinceañera
is the only weapon I have.

02:18.921 --> 02:20.227
I've gotta try.

02:20.270 --> 02:23.317
[upbeat Latin music]

02:30.193 --> 02:34.241
- Okay, so the million-dollar
question is

02:34.284 --> 02:39.202
pink and turquoise
or purple and gold?

02:39.246 --> 02:40.769
- We need you to break the tie

02:40.812 --> 02:44.164
and I promise we won't try
to influence you either way.

02:44.207 --> 02:46.209
- Okay, okay.
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, mm-hmm?

02:46.253 --> 02:48.646
- [inhales deeply]

02:48.690 --> 02:50.692
I gotta say, I love the pink.
- Yes!

02:50.735 --> 02:51.997
- Pink?
- I'm sorry!

02:52.041 --> 02:54.522
- Oh, I knew I loved this girl.
- [chuckles]

02:54.565 --> 02:57.307
- [laughs] Okay, so now we have
to talk about music.

02:57.351 --> 02:59.396
- I was thinking
we'd take a run at Mateo.

02:59.440 --> 03:00.484
- Ooh, mamita.

03:00.528 --> 03:01.659
I don't know
if that's a good idea.

03:01.703 --> 03:02.921
He's pretty serious
about being done.

03:02.965 --> 03:04.662
- I've known him for 15 years.

03:04.706 --> 03:07.491
I've got tons of dirt
and I'm not above blackmail.

03:07.535 --> 03:09.276
[laughter]

03:09.319 --> 03:10.407
- Mari.

03:10.451 --> 03:11.930
- Yeah.

03:11.974 --> 03:13.454
Hi.

03:13.497 --> 03:15.456
How'd it go with the inspector?

03:15.499 --> 03:16.457
- The good news is,

03:16.500 --> 03:17.936
we got the all clear to reopen

03:17.980 --> 03:21.984
as soon as the renovation's
done, so two weeks?

03:22.027 --> 03:23.377
- But there's bad news?

03:23.420 --> 03:25.509
- The price of the renovation
has doubled

03:25.553 --> 03:26.728
because of the extra work.
- [scoffs]

03:26.771 --> 03:27.990
What are we gonna do?

03:28.033 --> 03:30.514
- [sighs]
I'm sorry, Natalie.

03:30.558 --> 03:33.865
Your quinceañera's
gonna have to wait.

03:33.909 --> 03:35.563
- What?
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

03:35.606 --> 03:37.565
This is practically
a dieciséisañera.

03:37.608 --> 03:39.349
- Mari, do I look happy to you?

03:39.393 --> 03:40.394
We have no money.

03:40.437 --> 03:41.395
- We can put it
on a credit card.

03:41.438 --> 03:42.700
- They're all maxed out.

03:42.744 --> 03:44.354
- Por favor, there has
to be another way.

03:44.398 --> 03:46.051
- I'm sorry.

03:46.095 --> 03:47.879
I've made the decision because
it's the only decision to make.

03:47.923 --> 03:50.752
[downbeat music]

03:50.795 --> 03:52.710
- Mom.
- Mari.

03:52.754 --> 03:54.016
Mari.

03:54.059 --> 03:57.672
♪

03:57.715 --> 03:59.717
- We can't let this happen.

03:59.761 --> 04:02.459
We need this quinceañera now
more than ever.

04:02.503 --> 04:03.895
My family needs it.

04:03.939 --> 04:05.636
- Maybe we could start
a GoFundMe page.

04:05.680 --> 04:09.727
- We'd need
a lot more than that--ooh.

04:09.771 --> 04:12.513
- Wh-what?

04:12.556 --> 04:13.818
- I think I know a way

04:13.862 --> 04:17.605
we can solve all the Garcias'
problems at once.

04:17.648 --> 04:19.520
- Somebody order soup?

04:19.563 --> 04:22.436
- Oh, I'm starving.
Great.

04:22.479 --> 04:24.525
- This is my specialty.

04:24.568 --> 04:26.744
- Oh, you made this yourself,
did you?

04:26.788 --> 04:28.268
- Of course.

04:28.311 --> 04:30.748
I told you, everything
I brought you, I made myself.

04:30.792 --> 04:31.967
- Mm-huh.

04:32.010 --> 04:33.882
Well, judging by my taste buds,

04:33.925 --> 04:37.277
I would say that you've got
every great chef in Miami

04:37.320 --> 04:38.495
on standby.

04:38.539 --> 04:41.933
- Well, I love you
and you deserve the best.

04:41.977 --> 04:43.805
- But Noa, really,
giving me your bedroom?

04:43.848 --> 04:44.936
- What?

04:44.980 --> 04:46.373
This is the best mattress
in the house.

04:46.416 --> 04:48.462
- I appreciate the Florence
Nightingale treatment,

04:48.505 --> 04:51.813
but I'm just curious if
between prepping for the movie

04:51.856 --> 04:53.771
and taking care of me,

04:53.815 --> 04:56.948
you're not running away from
baker boy just a little bit?

04:56.992 --> 04:58.689
- Lewis, you know
I don't have time for that.

04:58.733 --> 05:00.952
- Oh, come on.
You're not a robot.

05:00.996 --> 05:02.650
- I thought
you didn't like him.

05:02.693 --> 05:03.999
- Well, you do.

05:04.042 --> 05:06.349
- Look what was happening
to his life and to mine.

05:06.393 --> 05:08.525
It was like the universe
was giving us signs.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.788
- No, I don't believe in signs.
[phone buzzes]

05:10.832 --> 05:13.008
[soft music]

05:13.051 --> 05:14.923
- Oh, wow.
- What?

05:14.966 --> 05:17.752
- I think another superfan
jumped the fence.

05:17.795 --> 05:19.971
Wait, is that Natalie?
- Oh.

05:20.015 --> 05:22.060
♪

05:22.104 --> 05:24.367
- It's a sign.

05:24.411 --> 05:27.370
What?
I-I believe in signs now.

05:27.414 --> 05:29.503
♪

05:29.546 --> 05:30.939
- I don't know if
I should be impressed with Mom

05:30.982 --> 05:32.810
or really worried about her.

05:32.854 --> 05:34.986
- Great, thank you.

05:35.030 --> 05:37.989
[sighs] I just locked down
the gazebo at Centennial Park.

05:38.033 --> 05:39.513
- Great, we can show up early

05:39.556 --> 05:40.905
and scrape off the dried
chewing gum.

05:40.949 --> 05:42.994
- Bro, we have
to think positive.

05:43.038 --> 05:45.127
We cannot let Natalie go
without a quinceañera.

05:45.170 --> 05:46.650
We have the venue,

05:46.694 --> 05:49.131
let's call our cousins, tell
them it's a potluck, and BYOB.

05:49.174 --> 05:50.132
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm,

05:50.175 --> 05:51.568
that sounds janky.

05:51.612 --> 05:52.830
- Maybe we could hang up some
Christmas lights, like,

05:52.874 --> 05:53.831
have a really nice vibe.

05:53.875 --> 05:55.616
- Yes, that sounds jankier.

05:55.659 --> 05:56.617
- Mateo.
- What?

05:56.660 --> 05:57.966
- But it's a plan, okay?

05:58.009 --> 05:59.794
It might sound janky,
but at least it's a plan.

05:59.837 --> 06:01.970
- Uh, I think
I've got a better one.

06:02.013 --> 06:04.712
♪

06:04.755 --> 06:08.672
- Noa?

06:08.716 --> 06:09.891
- Hi, Daniel.

06:13.590 --> 06:14.548
- I can't believe you did this.

06:14.591 --> 06:16.027
It's wrong on so many levels.

06:16.071 --> 06:17.768
- Daniel, who else do we know

06:17.812 --> 06:19.379
who can snap her fingers and--

06:19.422 --> 06:21.032
voila, a kickass party?

06:21.076 --> 06:23.034
- Me and Mateo
were already planning a party.

06:23.078 --> 06:25.341
- That would kick no ass.

06:29.432 --> 06:32.435
- I appreciate you coming,
but we can't take your charity.

06:32.479 --> 06:35.525
- It's not charity.
It's me helping a friend.

06:35.569 --> 06:37.962
Like you helped me
in Puerto Rico.

06:38.006 --> 06:40.661
- We were together then.
We're not now.

06:40.704 --> 06:42.619
You broke it off, remember?

06:42.663 --> 06:44.926
- Come on, Natalie's had
a really hard year.

06:44.969 --> 06:47.798
New school,
being outed by a dinner guest

06:47.842 --> 06:51.846
who'd like to make it up
to her?

06:51.889 --> 06:54.892
Besides, I still owe you
that third wish.

06:54.936 --> 06:58.113
[soft dramatic music]

06:58.156 --> 07:03.684
♪

07:03.727 --> 07:04.685
- Okay.

07:04.728 --> 07:06.469
- [cheers]
- Yes!

07:06.513 --> 07:08.123
- Hey, hey!
Okay, okay.

07:08.166 --> 07:09.341
We have a lot
of work to do.

07:09.385 --> 07:10.734
I got to call
my party planner,

07:10.778 --> 07:12.344
the florist, the caterer.

07:12.388 --> 07:13.737
We need a venue.

07:13.781 --> 07:15.435
- Wait, we can use the café.

07:15.478 --> 07:17.349
And Daniel can bake the cake.

07:17.393 --> 07:20.831
♪

07:20.875 --> 07:22.093
- Of course.

07:22.137 --> 07:24.052
- And Mateo will DJ.
- Mm-hmm.

07:24.095 --> 07:26.010
[music pauses]

07:26.054 --> 07:28.099
I really
appreciate you asking.

07:28.143 --> 07:31.538
- Mateo, my quinceañera
won't be my quinceañera

07:31.581 --> 07:33.844
if I don't have MC Cubano.

07:33.888 --> 07:35.846
- [sighs]

07:35.890 --> 07:36.934
What can I say?

07:36.978 --> 07:39.023
When you're right,
you're right.

07:39.067 --> 07:42.505
- So yes?

07:42.549 --> 07:43.506
- Yes.

07:43.550 --> 07:45.552
[chuckling]

07:45.595 --> 07:48.032
[upbeat music]

07:48.076 --> 07:50.687
♪

07:50.731 --> 07:53.777
- Hey, Vanessa.
I thought you sold the place.

07:53.821 --> 07:56.127
- Oh, um...

07:56.171 --> 07:57.651
Yeah,

07:57.694 --> 07:59.043
the buyers cancelled escrow
when they couldn't get a loan,

07:59.087 --> 08:02.525
so now I have till the end
of the week to sell it again

08:02.569 --> 08:04.875
or Eli Weiss is canceling me.

08:04.919 --> 08:06.007
[chuckles]
Yeah.

08:06.050 --> 08:08.444
- That sucks.
I'm sorry.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.533
Sounds like you need a party.

08:10.577 --> 08:13.536
Come to Natalie's quinceañera.
- [scoffs]

08:13.580 --> 08:16.147
Mateo...

08:16.191 --> 08:18.715
is that a good idea, like?

08:18.759 --> 08:21.892
- Why wouldn't it be?

08:21.936 --> 08:25.026
MC Cubano is coming out of
retirement for one night only

08:25.069 --> 08:27.550
as a gift to Natalie.

08:27.594 --> 08:30.771
So wouldn't it make sense for
his former manager to be there?

08:30.814 --> 08:33.164
- [groans]
- Come on.

08:33.208 --> 08:35.166
Vanessa, I've missed you

08:35.210 --> 08:38.126
and you know my live sets
are better than any other set.

08:39.954 --> 08:42.826
- Wait a minute, you're right.

08:42.870 --> 08:45.742
Live MC Cubano is better
than studio MC Cubano,

08:45.786 --> 08:47.918
especially considering
his studio is in a closet.

08:47.962 --> 08:49.964
- Okay--
- That's what Marlowe needs.

08:50.007 --> 08:50.965
He needs to see you
in the flesh.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.444
- Come on, V.
- Yes!

08:52.488 --> 08:53.620
- No,
he made it absolutely clear,

08:53.663 --> 08:54.708
I don't got what it takes.

08:54.751 --> 08:56.448
- Because he didn't
see you live.

08:56.492 --> 08:59.234
And I wasn't standing
next to you

08:59.277 --> 09:01.671
when you met with him.

09:01.715 --> 09:03.978
[soft dramatic music]

09:04.021 --> 09:05.632
♪

09:05.675 --> 09:08.548
This weekend, I will be.

09:08.591 --> 09:11.246
Come on, you said it yourself,
it's a one-time thing.

09:11.289 --> 09:13.117
It's you rocking out
for Natalie

09:13.161 --> 09:15.816
on her special night
and dropping the mic.

09:15.859 --> 09:18.253
We'll go big or we'll go home.

09:18.296 --> 09:19.646
Eh?

09:19.689 --> 09:21.082
Come on.

09:21.125 --> 09:23.911
Mateo, trust me.

09:25.129 --> 09:28.742
- Yeah, okay, let's do it.
- Yes, yes!

09:28.785 --> 09:32.572
- There is one tiny, little,
insignificant thing

09:32.615 --> 09:34.486
I should tell you
about the party.

09:34.530 --> 09:36.097
- What?

09:36.140 --> 09:40.275
- Noa Hamilton is throwing it?
- And MC Cubano is spinning.

09:40.318 --> 09:43.539
I mean, what can I say?
The woman knows talent.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.715
- I don't know, Vanessa.

09:45.759 --> 09:47.674
- Johnny Cash at San Quentin,

09:47.717 --> 09:49.501
Jimi Hendrix at Woodstock,

09:49.545 --> 09:51.634
Queen at Live Aid.

09:51.678 --> 09:54.115
These artists defined
their careers

09:54.158 --> 09:57.814
by the connection they made
with their live audience.

09:57.858 --> 09:59.642
- You really think
this guy's that good?

09:59.686 --> 10:02.166
- I think he could be, yeah.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.951
With your help.

10:03.994 --> 10:05.735
I think you were quick
to judge.

10:05.779 --> 10:08.999
So all I'm saying
is come and see him live,

10:09.043 --> 10:11.045
then decide.

10:12.089 --> 10:14.526
- Okay.

10:14.570 --> 10:16.616
I'll come.
- Really?

10:16.659 --> 10:17.660
- As your date.

10:17.704 --> 10:20.620
[soft dramatic music]

10:20.663 --> 10:21.925
- Really?

10:23.100 --> 10:25.625
- I started putting
that book together

10:25.668 --> 10:28.149
before Natalie was born.

10:28.192 --> 10:31.674
As soon as I found out
I was having a girl.

10:31.718 --> 10:33.763
15 years of planning.

10:35.330 --> 10:38.159
And now because
my family lacks the means

10:38.202 --> 10:40.074
to make my dream
for my daughter come true,

10:40.117 --> 10:43.730
you want to swoop in
and make it all happen?

10:49.736 --> 10:52.042
Thank you so much.

10:52.086 --> 10:54.175
Thank you from the bottom
of my heart!

10:54.218 --> 10:58.658
Thank you so much.
- My pleasure, my pleasure!

10:58.701 --> 11:00.311
- [sighs]

11:00.355 --> 11:02.836
- What's all this?
- Dad, I've been calling you.

11:02.879 --> 11:05.752
- Rafael,
a miracle has happened.

11:05.795 --> 11:07.710
The quinces is back on.

11:07.754 --> 11:10.234
Noa is donating the party
as her gift.

11:10.278 --> 11:12.062
♪

11:12.106 --> 11:14.891
- And I'm good with it.

11:14.935 --> 11:16.937
- You are?

11:16.980 --> 11:18.982
Well, I'm not.

11:19.026 --> 11:21.071
The Garcias don't take charity.

11:21.115 --> 11:22.159
- That's what Daniel said,
but Mr. Garcia,

11:22.203 --> 11:23.639
this isn't charity, I--

11:23.683 --> 11:25.772
- Thank you but no thank you
for your generous offer.

11:25.815 --> 11:28.949
And no, I don't want
to talk about this anymore.

11:28.992 --> 11:31.212
- Rafael, perdóname.

11:31.255 --> 11:34.737
I am not going to let you turn
this into a Cuban macho thing.

11:34.781 --> 11:35.782
- You think
that's what I'm doing?

11:35.825 --> 11:37.784
- Yes, I do.

11:37.827 --> 11:40.047
You can't afford
to throw your daughter a party,

11:40.090 --> 11:41.831
but you don't want anyone else
to do it.

11:41.875 --> 11:43.877
- You're right, Mari,
I can't afford it.

11:43.920 --> 11:45.139
You know why?

11:45.182 --> 11:47.402
Because of the hole
that you got us into.

11:47.445 --> 11:48.708
- That I dug us into?

11:48.751 --> 11:49.752
- Yes, you.
- [scoffs]

11:49.796 --> 11:51.145
- You pushed
for this renovation,

11:51.188 --> 11:52.755
and pushed, and pushed,
and pushed.

11:52.799 --> 11:54.626
- You wanted to move forward
just as much as I did.

11:54.670 --> 11:55.802
- No.
- Yes, you did!

11:55.845 --> 11:57.412
- What I wanted was for you
to be happy.

11:57.455 --> 12:00.371
I was fine with what we had.
You wanted more.

12:00.415 --> 12:02.286
And now,
we can lose everything.

12:02.330 --> 12:04.375
- You can do whatever
you want to do, Rafael,

12:04.419 --> 12:06.769
but we are having
this quinceañera,

12:06.813 --> 12:08.379
and I am making the decision

12:08.423 --> 12:10.817
because it's the only one
to make.

12:13.689 --> 12:16.648
[soft dramatic music]

12:16.692 --> 12:18.868
♪

12:22.350 --> 12:25.266
[upbeat music]

12:25.309 --> 12:26.833
♪

12:26.876 --> 12:30.619
- I'm so glad Natalie wanted
to use this expansion space.

12:30.662 --> 12:33.840
It's like a way
to get rid of all the bad juju.

12:33.883 --> 12:36.843
- Maybe it'll make your dad feel
less like he's taking charity.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.888
- [sighs]

12:38.932 --> 12:40.934
- Speaking of, I take it

12:40.977 --> 12:43.806
he and your mom
haven't made up yet.

12:43.850 --> 12:45.025
- Remember when I told you

12:45.068 --> 12:47.810
that my parents
have all this passion?

12:47.854 --> 12:49.812
It's great
until they start fighting,

12:49.856 --> 12:51.248
then it's like
"Clash of the Titans."

12:51.292 --> 12:54.034
Neither one give an inch.

12:54.077 --> 12:57.254
- I guess, even in
the best relationships,

