♪

27:46.882 --> 27:48.492
And then I blinked.

27:48.536 --> 27:50.538
[soft dramatic music]

27:50.581 --> 27:54.716
And ten years of tomorrows
have gone by.

27:54.760 --> 27:58.633
♪

27:58.677 --> 28:00.679
I just want to matter
to someone.

28:00.722 --> 28:04.117
Really matter.

28:04.160 --> 28:06.641
And have them matter to me.

28:06.685 --> 28:10.645
♪

28:10.689 --> 28:12.734
- Well,
I just want you for your body.

28:12.778 --> 28:14.780
- [laughs]

28:14.823 --> 28:16.738
♪

28:16.782 --> 28:18.609
- But I--I suppose I could be
talked into

28:18.653 --> 28:21.961
spending time together,

28:22.004 --> 28:23.963
seeing what happens.

28:24.006 --> 28:26.487
- [sighs]

28:26.530 --> 28:29.577
[indistinct chatter]

28:32.058 --> 28:35.757
- There are a lot of people
that I need to thank tonight,

28:35.801 --> 28:39.761
like my own personal
fairy godmother, Noa Hamilton.

28:39.805 --> 28:42.982
[cheers and applause]

28:43.025 --> 28:46.725
People say that you shouldn't
meet your heroes, but

28:46.768 --> 28:48.639
she's everything
I dreamed she would be.

28:48.683 --> 28:50.511
[cheers and applause]

28:50.554 --> 28:53.644
Most importantly,
I'd like to thank my brothers,

28:53.688 --> 28:57.257
the best brothers
in the whole world.

28:57.300 --> 29:00.782
And to the people that without
whom there would be no quince

29:00.826 --> 29:02.784
because there would be no me,

29:02.828 --> 29:06.701
my parents,
Mari and Rafael Garcia.

29:06.745 --> 29:08.834
[cheers and applause]

29:08.877 --> 29:10.879
Mom, come up here.
Come up.

29:10.923 --> 29:13.577
[cheers and applause]

29:16.667 --> 29:19.148
Tonight is not just about me,

29:19.192 --> 29:22.021
it's about celebrating
the people who made me.

29:23.849 --> 29:26.765
[Gloria Estefan's
"Con los Años Que Me Quedan"]

29:26.808 --> 29:33.772
♪

29:33.815 --> 29:38.820
- ♪ Sé que aún

29:38.864 --> 29:42.824
♪ Me queda una oportunidad

29:42.868 --> 29:44.304
♪

29:44.347 --> 29:49.831
♪ Sé que aún no es tarde

29:49.875 --> 29:55.228
♪ Para recapacitar

29:55.271 --> 30:00.363
♪ Sé que nuestro amor

30:00.407 --> 30:05.368
♪ Es verdadero

30:05.412 --> 30:07.327
♪ Y con los años

30:07.370 --> 30:12.201
♪ Que me quedan por vivir

30:12.245 --> 30:16.815
♪ Demostraré

30:16.858 --> 30:21.863
♪ Cuánto te quiero

30:21.907 --> 30:28.696
♪

30:28.739 --> 30:31.090
♪ Con los años
que me quedan ♪

30:31.133 --> 30:33.701
- Enough, Rafael!

30:33.744 --> 30:35.921
We've both been acting
like big babies.

30:35.964 --> 30:38.924
I'm sorry for what I said.

30:38.967 --> 30:42.014
I'm sorry, okay?
I'm sorry.

30:42.057 --> 30:44.103
- ♪ Con besos llenos
de pasión ♪

30:44.146 --> 30:47.846
- Rafael.

30:47.889 --> 30:50.849
[speaking Spanish]

30:52.154 --> 30:55.331
- Do you remember that song?

30:55.375 --> 30:56.898
- Of course I remember it.

30:56.942 --> 30:59.292
It was playing
the night we met.

30:59.335 --> 31:01.772
- It was playing
the night we left.

31:01.816 --> 31:03.644
- ♪ No quise herirte,
mi amor ♪

31:03.687 --> 31:07.691
- We gave up everything
when we left Havana

31:07.735 --> 31:10.912
to give our children
a better life.

31:10.956 --> 31:12.958
- No, we found our way.

31:13.001 --> 31:14.829
♪

31:14.873 --> 31:17.876
- People are fickle, Mari.

31:17.919 --> 31:20.966
What we reopen those doors
and nobody comes back?

31:21.009 --> 31:23.011
What if this is the biggest
crowd we ever get?

31:23.055 --> 31:25.971
- Even if we lost

31:26.014 --> 31:31.019
every last cup of flour
in this bakery,

31:31.063 --> 31:34.153
we will always have each other.

31:34.196 --> 31:38.331
And that will always be
more than anything to me.

31:38.374 --> 31:39.898
♪

31:43.205 --> 31:45.991
[chuckles softly]

31:46.034 --> 31:48.297
You haven't called me that
in a long time.

31:48.341 --> 31:50.952
- [sighs]

31:50.996 --> 31:52.388
- I've missed it.

31:58.394 --> 32:02.877
- ♪ Como comprobar que
no soy quien fui ♪

32:02.921 --> 32:05.053
♪ Tiempo te dirá

32:05.097 --> 32:08.187
♪ Si tienes fe en mí

32:08.230 --> 32:11.930
♪ Que como yo te amé

32:11.973 --> 32:15.063
♪ Más nadie

32:15.107 --> 32:17.936
♪ Te podrá amar jamás

32:17.979 --> 32:22.418
♪ Me que no es el final

32:22.462 --> 32:23.942
♪

32:23.985 --> 32:28.947
♪ Sé que aún

32:28.990 --> 32:32.080
♪ Me queda una oportunidad

32:35.866 --> 32:36.998
- And Mateo
was totally embarrassed.

32:37.042 --> 32:37.956
It was the best day
of my life, yeah.

32:37.999 --> 32:38.957
[laughter]

32:39.000 --> 32:40.480
- So your slideshow worked.

32:40.523 --> 32:42.351
I saw your parents making out
in the kitchen.

32:42.395 --> 32:43.874
- Oh, my God.
I'm sorry.

32:43.918 --> 32:45.137
Do you need
to have your memory erased?

32:45.180 --> 32:46.268
- No.
[laughs]

32:46.312 --> 32:48.183
And Mateo's set
was a huge success.

32:48.227 --> 32:49.968
MC Cubano is back.

32:50.011 --> 32:53.101
- So that just leaves
one thing.

32:53.145 --> 32:54.581
- Daniel and Noa.

32:54.624 --> 32:58.193
- Actually, I was gonna say
a dance with my girlfriend.

32:58.237 --> 33:00.195
- Really?

33:00.239 --> 33:03.024
Are you worried
with all your relatives here?

33:03.068 --> 33:05.853
- It's my quince.
I get what I want.

33:05.896 --> 33:07.072
- [chuckles]

33:07.115 --> 33:09.509
- May I?
- You may.

33:09.552 --> 33:11.467
[Sigrid's "Mine Right Now"

33:11.511 --> 33:16.211
- ♪ Then I ruin the moment
'cause I picture the end ♪

33:16.255 --> 33:20.868
♪ But I don't wanna go there,
so I tell myself that ♪

33:20.911 --> 33:25.873
♪ Hey, it's all right
if we don't end up together ♪

33:25.916 --> 33:28.006
♪

33:28.049 --> 33:30.008
♪ 'Cause you're mine
right now ♪

33:30.051 --> 33:31.400
♪ Hey

33:31.444 --> 33:36.057
♪ I don't mind
if we don't get to forever ♪

33:36.101 --> 33:37.363
♪

33:37.406 --> 33:39.060
♪ 'Cause you're mine
right now ♪

33:39.104 --> 33:40.888
- Where's Marlowe?

33:40.931 --> 33:44.065
- ♪ It's all right if we don't
end up staying together ♪

33:44.109 --> 33:46.328
♪ It's all right if we don't

33:46.372 --> 33:48.330
- I don't know.

33:48.374 --> 33:50.854
♪

33:50.898 --> 33:53.988
We were having a great time.

33:54.032 --> 33:57.252
He loved your set.
- [chuckles]

33:57.296 --> 34:00.081
- But then poof,
he's gone.

34:00.125 --> 34:02.562
♪

34:02.605 --> 34:08.002
- It wasn't your fault, I--

34:08.046 --> 34:10.048
think it's his loss.

34:10.091 --> 34:13.486
- [chuckles softly]

34:13.529 --> 34:15.879
- ♪ But I don't wanna
go there ♪

34:15.923 --> 34:18.012
♪ So I tell myself that

34:18.056 --> 34:22.886
- A few months ago,
I saw my future so clearly.

34:22.930 --> 34:27.326
Now I have no idea
what my future is.

34:27.369 --> 34:29.502
♪

34:29.545 --> 34:32.113
I'm just

34:32.157 --> 34:34.115
failing my way through life.

34:34.159 --> 34:38.467
- Failing?
Are you crazy?

34:38.511 --> 34:40.078
I mean, you gave me a chance
at my dream.

34:40.121 --> 34:43.472
- You got that for yourself.

34:43.516 --> 34:46.606
I just saw what you had.

34:46.649 --> 34:49.435
Vanessa has vision,
just like the ad says.

34:49.478 --> 34:50.827
[chuckles]

34:50.871 --> 34:52.568
- Vanessa,
let's get out of here.

34:52.612 --> 34:55.049
- At least my vision
helps people.

34:55.093 --> 34:56.442
That, I feel good about.

34:56.485 --> 34:58.444
- Vanessa.

34:58.487 --> 35:01.316
♪

35:01.360 --> 35:03.144
- Mateo, no.

35:03.188 --> 35:05.103
- Vanessa,
it's--it's nothing like that.

35:05.146 --> 35:07.322
- ♪ It's all right if we don't
end up staying together ♪

35:07.366 --> 35:09.933
- There's a place I want
to take you to.

35:09.977 --> 35:12.501
- ♪ It's all right
if we don't ♪

35:12.545 --> 35:15.156
- What are we doing
in the house I can't sell?

35:15.200 --> 35:17.158
- We're celebrating.

35:17.202 --> 35:19.334
- I was saving that
for when I found a buyer.

35:19.378 --> 35:20.596
- Oh, perfect timing.
[cork pops]

35:20.640 --> 35:22.859
'Cause I found a buyer:

35:22.903 --> 35:25.166
You.
- [scoffs]

35:25.210 --> 35:26.341
You're crazy.

35:26.385 --> 35:29.127
- [chuckles]
No, I'm not.

35:29.170 --> 35:32.652
You've always believed in me,
no matter what.

35:32.695 --> 35:34.915
Now it's my turn
to believe in you.

35:37.135 --> 35:39.398
Yup.

35:39.441 --> 35:42.183
Yeah, you can do this.

35:42.227 --> 35:44.664
You can flip this house.

35:44.707 --> 35:48.494
You can flip it, fix it up,
sell it for double.

35:48.537 --> 35:49.973
- [laughs]
Mateo.

35:50.017 --> 35:51.540
- You know what I've always
liked about you?

35:51.584 --> 35:53.542
There's nothing you can't do.

35:53.586 --> 35:56.371
What do you know
about the music industry?

35:56.415 --> 35:57.677
Nada.

35:57.720 --> 35:59.374
And yet, you got
Marlowe St. John to back me.

35:59.418 --> 36:02.682
- That's true.
- [chuckles]

36:02.725 --> 36:06.207
You see value
where others don't.

36:06.251 --> 36:08.209
♪

36:08.253 --> 36:12.213
So stop selling that vision
to other people.

36:12.257 --> 36:15.216
Use it
to build your own empire.

36:15.260 --> 36:17.523
[soft dramatic music]

36:17.566 --> 36:19.351
♪

36:19.394 --> 36:21.527
- I never thought
I'd use these words.

36:21.570 --> 36:24.007
- Yes?
- But you're right.

36:24.051 --> 36:25.574
[chuckles softly]

36:25.618 --> 36:27.402
You...

36:27.446 --> 36:29.230
are...

36:29.274 --> 36:30.275
right.

36:30.318 --> 36:32.102
♪

36:32.146 --> 36:34.148
[sighs]

36:34.192 --> 36:37.238
I have to update
all the kitchen appliances,

36:37.282 --> 36:38.457
first of all.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.459
And then change
the kitchen countertop,

36:40.502 --> 36:44.027
and maybe put in accent wall
here and subway tiles there.

36:44.071 --> 36:46.421
I mean, Mateo--
[laughing] you're brilliant.

36:46.465 --> 36:47.770
- I'll leave you to it.

36:47.814 --> 36:50.947
- And then I'd make
the whole back wall glass.

36:50.991 --> 36:54.734
And I'd rip up the floors
and--and put down hard wood.

36:54.777 --> 36:56.431
But...

36:56.475 --> 36:59.434
I did not say you could go.

36:59.478 --> 37:02.437
[upbeat dramatic music]

37:02.481 --> 37:05.745
♪

37:05.788 --> 37:07.442
- One, two, three.

37:07.486 --> 37:09.488
Now funny face.

37:09.531 --> 37:11.229
[chuckles]

37:11.272 --> 37:12.752
- Thank you, thank you,
thank you!

37:12.795 --> 37:16.451
- You're welcome.
[laughs]

37:16.495 --> 37:21.456
- Thank you for taking selfies
with all 32 of my cousins.

37:21.500 --> 37:24.067
- They're adorable.

37:24.111 --> 37:25.634
Did Natalie enjoy the night?

37:25.678 --> 37:27.201
- The best.

37:27.245 --> 37:29.682
Hey, she told me that Amy
caught my parents making out,

37:29.725 --> 37:31.118
so it's a win-win.

37:31.161 --> 37:33.163
- [sighs]
- [chuckles]

37:33.207 --> 37:36.079
- You're so lucky
to have a family like this.

37:37.342 --> 37:39.648
It was really nice
being a part of it again,

37:39.692 --> 37:43.173
even if it was just
for one night.

37:43.217 --> 37:45.175
[soft dramatic music]

37:45.219 --> 37:49.745
I have this belief that you
can't have everything in life,

37:49.789 --> 37:53.662
like I can't have
this fairy tale existence

37:53.706 --> 37:56.665
and a happy ending.

37:56.709 --> 38:00.582
And I'm seeing now
that that's just a belief.

38:00.626 --> 38:03.324
It's very limiting and has
a lot to do with how I grew up.

38:03.368 --> 38:05.413
Has a lot to do
with how I grew up.

38:05.457 --> 38:07.807
- Noa.

38:07.850 --> 38:13.116
- I have never been happier
than I was when I was with you.

38:13.160 --> 38:15.423
You make me laugh.

38:15.467 --> 38:18.470
You remind me not
to take myself so seriously.

38:18.513 --> 38:20.385
- [chuckles]

38:20.428 --> 38:24.302
- You're everything
that I never had...

38:24.345 --> 38:29.176
and I'm sorry I got scared
and I blew it.

38:29.219 --> 38:33.354
[sighs]
Can you please forgive me?

38:33.398 --> 38:35.356
- I do forgive you.

38:35.400 --> 38:37.358
- [chuckles softly]

38:37.402 --> 38:38.751
♪

38:38.794 --> 38:42.189
- But you're going to Morocco
for three months,

38:42.232 --> 38:45.366
and my family needs me here.

38:45.410 --> 38:47.368
I don't want photographers
following me around.

38:47.412 --> 38:48.630
I don't want to spend my life

38:48.674 --> 38:50.719
traveling to events
and parties.

38:50.763 --> 38:54.375
I want nights like tonight.

38:54.419 --> 38:57.726
I never realized how much
I enjoyed normal life

38:57.770 --> 39:00.599
until I left it.

39:00.642 --> 39:02.383
It was so much fun

39:02.427 --> 39:04.777
being up there
in the stratosphere with you...

39:04.820 --> 39:06.779
♪

39:06.822 --> 39:11.392
But I'm back now.
On Earth.

39:11.436 --> 39:13.394
Where I belong.

39:13.438 --> 39:17.398
♪

39:17.442 --> 39:19.400
- [breathes deeply]

39:19.444 --> 39:21.837
♪

39:21.881 --> 39:24.840
I get it.

39:24.884 --> 39:26.842
I do.

39:26.886 --> 39:32.761
♪

39:32.805 --> 39:35.373
Thank you.

39:35.416 --> 39:42.423
♪

39:53.739 --> 39:56.698
[Gloria Estefan's "Con Los
Años Que Me Quedan" playing]

39:56.742 --> 40:03.792
♪

40:04.837 --> 40:10.364
- ♪ Sé que aún no es tarde

40:10.408 --> 40:13.715
♪ Para recapacitar

40:16.675 --> 40:17.893
- Lewis.

40:17.937 --> 40:20.418
Don't worry,
I'm closing my eyes.

40:24.204 --> 40:26.380
Lewis?

40:26.424 --> 40:27.686
♪

40:27.729 --> 40:29.775
[cell phone chimes]

40:31.385 --> 40:33.822
[soft upbeat music]

40:33.866 --> 40:37.260
♪

40:37.304 --> 40:38.958
- [laughs]

40:39.001 --> 40:41.482
[indistinct chatter]

40:41.526 --> 40:42.744
- [laughs]

40:42.788 --> 40:49.838
♪

40:54.974 --> 40:58.194
- Ahh, the Cook-izza.

40:58.238 --> 41:03.330
I've heard tale of this
magical culinary combination.

41:03.373 --> 41:06.507
- Thomas Gold.

41:06.551 --> 41:08.466
Are you reviewing a Duffigan's?

41:08.509 --> 41:10.555
- No, your father told me
where I could find you.

41:10.598 --> 41:12.600
I have to admit,
I was surprised.

41:12.644 --> 41:16.778
You're a long way away
from the Pastelito Magnifico.

41:16.822 --> 41:19.302
- Yeah, it's just a gig
to help pay down the bills

41:19.346 --> 41:20.565
until we reopen the bakery.

41:20.608 --> 41:23.524
- Yeah, how about...

41:23.568 --> 41:25.439
another gig?

41:25.483 --> 41:28.573
Couple of my readers forwarded
me some of your videos.

41:28.616 --> 41:31.706
I think there might
be an opportunity

41:31.750 --> 41:33.403
for us to work together.

41:33.447 --> 41:37.538
♪

41:37.582 --> 41:39.540
- [chuckles]

41:39.584 --> 41:43.718
♪

41:43.762 --> 41:46.721
[light guitar music]

41:46.765 --> 41:53.815
♪

42:09.875 --> 42:11.877
♪

42:15.576 --> 42:18.536
[upbeat music]

42:18.579 --> 42:25.586
♪
